definitions.definition: To move busily and energetically with fussiness (often followed by about ).
examples: The commuters bustled about inside the train station.

definitions.definition: To teem or abound (usually followed by with ); to exhibit an energetic and active abundance (of a thing).
examples: The train station was bustling with commuters.

main_definition: To move busily and energetically with fussiness (often followed by about ).
secondary_definitions: To teem or abound (usually followed by with ); to exhibit an energetic and active abundance (of a thing).
( transitive ) To push around , to importune .
